The outline-magic package by CarstenDominik ([https://melpa.org/#/outline-magic MELPA], [https://github.com/tj64/outline-magic GitHub]) extends OutlineMode and OutlineMinorMode.

After installing it into a location on your <code>load-path</code>, enable it with:

<pre>
(eval-after-load 'outline
  '(progn
    (require 'outline-magic)
    (define-key outline-minor-mode-map (kbd "<C-tab>") 'outline-cycle)))
</pre>

It provides four commands
for structure editing.  Using M-up, M-down, M-left, and M-right, you
can easily move entries around:

                               move up
                                  ^
                      promote  <- + ->  demote
                                  v
                              move down

You can also use outline-magic to fold python code:
* [http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4079648/combine-python-mode-with-org-mode-for-emacs/4093889#4093889 python-magic.el]
* http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/python-magic.el
